---
/**
 * Claude Code Getting Started — English Guide
 * Accessible via email link + focusai.co.il/claude-code-guide-en/
 * Route: /claude-code-guide-en/
 */
import Analytics from '../components/Analytics.astro';
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" dir="ltr">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Claude Code Getting Started Guide | Focus AI</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Complete beginner's guide to Claude Code — from installation to your first AI-assisted project with 50 professional skills.">
  <meta name="robots" content="noindex">
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon.png" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800;900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <Analytics slot="head" />
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    :root {
      --bg:      #dddcd4;
      --win-bg:  #ffffff;
      --win-bar: #d4d3cb;
      --text:    #1a1a14;
      --muted:   #55554e;
      --faint:   #888880;
      --orange:  #c8643c;
      --orange-h:#b8542c;
      --border:  #c8c7bf;
      --card-bg: #f8f8f4;
      --mono:    'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      --body-font: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    }

    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

    body {
      font-family: var(--body-font);
      background-color: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.7;
      overflow-x: hidden;
    }

    .wrap { max-width: 780px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }

    .topbar {
      background: var(--win-bar);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding: 12px 24px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
    }
    .topbar a { color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; }
    .topbar a:hover { color: var(--orange); }

    .hero {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 56px 24px 40px;
    }
    .hero-label {
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 2px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 48px);
      font-weight: 900;
      line-height: 1.15;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .hero-sub {
      font-size: 16px;
      color: var(--muted);
      max-width: 540px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .guide-body {
      background: var(--win-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      margin: 0 auto 40px;
      max-width: 780px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .doc-bar {
      background: var(--win-bar);
      padding: 10px 20px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
    }
    .doc-dot { width: 12px; height: 12px; border-radius: 50%; }
    .doc-dot.r { background: #ff5f57; }
    .doc-dot.y { background: #ffbd2e; }
    .doc-dot.g { background: #28c840; }
    .doc-title { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); margin-left: auto; }

    .doc-content { padding: 40px 48px 56px; }

    .doc-content h2 {
      font-size: clamp(18px, 3vw, 26px);
      font-weight: 800;
      margin: 48px 0 16px;
      padding-top: 32px;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .doc-content h2:first-child { border-top: none; padding-top: 0; margin-top: 0; }
    .doc-content h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; margin: 28px 0 10px; }
    .doc-content p { font-size: 15px; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 16px; line-height: 1.8; }
    .doc-content strong { color: var(--text); }
    .doc-content ul { margin: 0 0 16px 0; padding-left: 20px; }
    .doc-content li { font-size: 15px; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 8px; line-height: 1.7; }
    .doc-content ol { margin: 0 0 16px 0; padding-left: 20px; }
    .doc-content ol li { font-size: 15px; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .doc-content a { color: var(--orange); text-decoration: none; }
    .doc-content a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .step-num {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      width: 28px;
      height: 28px;
      background: var(--orange);
      color: #fff;
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 800;
      border-radius: 50%;
      margin-right: 8px;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }

    .code-block {
      background: #1e1e2e;
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 16px 20px;
      margin: 12px 0 20px;
      overflow-x: auto;
    }
    .code-block code {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 13px;
      color: #cdd6f4;
      line-height: 1.7;
      white-space: pre;
      display: block;
    }
    .comment { color: #6c7086; }
    .cmd { color: #89dceb; }

    .ic {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 13px;
      background: #eee;
      padding: 2px 6px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      color: #c8643c;
    }

    .tbl {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin: 12px 0 24px;
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    .tbl th {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      padding: 10px 14px;
      text-align: left;
      font-weight: 700;
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border);
    }
    .tbl td {
      padding: 10px 14px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      color: var(--muted);
      vertical-align: top;
    }
    .tbl tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    .tbl td:first-child { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--orange); }

    .note {
      background: #fef9f0;
      border-left: 3px solid #e8a953;
      padding: 12px 16px;
      border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
      margin: 16px 0;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .note strong { color: #b8732c; }

    .skill-table {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 8px;
      margin: 12px 0 24px;
    }
    .skill-item {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 6px;
      padding: 10px 14px;
    }
    .skill-cmd {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 12px;
      color: var(--orange);
      font-weight: 600;
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 2px;
    }
    .skill-desc { font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.4; }

    @media (max-width: 580px) {
      .skill-table { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .doc-content { padding: 24px 20px 40px; }
    }

    .cta-block {
      background: #1e1e2e;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 48px 40px;
      text-align: center;
      margin: 48px 0 0;
    }
    .cta-block h2 { color: #fff; font-size: clamp(20px, 4vw, 32px); margin-bottom: 12px; }
    .cta-block p { color: #9090a0; font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 28px; max-width: 480px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
    .btn-cta {
      display: inline-block;
      background: var(--orange);
      color: #fff;
      font-family: var(--body-font);
      font-size: 16px;
      font-weight: 700;
      padding: 16px 36px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      text-decoration: none;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(200,100,60,0.3);
    }
    .btn-cta:hover { background: var(--orange-h); }

    footer {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 32px 24px;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    footer a { color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-size: 13px; }
    footer a:hover { color: var(--orange); }
    .footer-links { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 24px; margin: 16px 0 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .footer-copy { font-size: 12px; color: var(--faint); }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <div class="topbar">
    <a href="https://focusai.co.il">← Back to Focus AI</a>
    <a href="/claude-code-guide/">גרסה בעברית ←</a>
  </div>

  <div class="hero">
    <img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dfudxxzlj/image/upload/q_auto,f_auto,h_64/v1772353512/FOCUS_LOGO-02_zmbrgf.jpg"
         alt="Focus AI" height="64" style="display:block;margin:0 auto 16px;">
    <p class="hero-label">Getting Started Guide</p>
    <h1>Claude Code — Zero to First Project</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">Installation, setup, and 50 professional skills ready to use. A complete guide for beginners.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="guide-body">

      <div class="doc-bar">
        <div class="doc-dot r"></div>
        <div class="doc-dot y"></div>
        <div class="doc-dot g"></div>
        <span class="doc-title">claude-code-getting-started-en.md</span>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-content">

        <h2>What Is Claude Code?</h2>
        <p>Claude Code is Anthropic's official CLI — an AI assistant that lives inside your terminal. Unlike ChatGPT or Claude.ai in the browser, Claude Code can <strong>read your files, write code, run commands, and edit your project</strong> — all from a conversation.</p>
        <p>It's the closest thing to having a senior developer sitting next to you.</p>

        <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
        <table class="tbl">
          <thead><tr><th>Requirement</th><th>Why</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>macOS / Linux / Windows</td><td>Claude Code runs in the terminal</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Node.js 18+</td><td>Claude Code is a Node.js package</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Anthropic API key</td><td>Claude Code uses the API to talk to Claude</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>Check if Node.js is installed:</p>
        <div class="code-block"><code>node --version</code></div>
        <p>If you see <span class="ic">v18.x.x</span> or higher — you're set. If not, download from <a href="https://nodejs.org" target="_blank">nodejs.org</a> (LTS version).</p>

        <h2><span class="step-num">1</span> Get Your Anthropic API Key</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Go to <a href="https://console.anthropic.com" target="_blank">console.anthropic.com</a></li>
          <li>Sign up or log in</li>
          <li>Click <strong>"Get API Keys"</strong> in the left sidebar</li>
          <li>Click <strong>"Create Key"</strong> → name it anything (e.g., "claude-code")</li>
          <li><strong>Copy the key</strong> — it starts with <span class="ic">sk-ant-...</span></li>
          <li>Save it somewhere safe — you won't be able to see it again</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="note">
          <strong>Billing note:</strong> Claude Code uses API credits. New accounts get free credits. After that, usage is pay-as-you-go — typically $2–10/month for regular developer use.
        </div>

        <h2><span class="step-num">2</span> Install Claude Code</h2>
        <div class="code-block"><code>npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code</code></div>
        <p>Verify the installation:</p>
        <div class="code-block"><code>claude --version</code></div>
        <p>You should see a version number like <span class="ic">1.x.x</span>.</p>

        <h2><span class="step-num">3</span> Authenticate</h2>
        <div class="code-block"><code>claude</code></div>
        <p>The first time you run this, Claude Code will ask for your API key. Paste the key from Step 1 and press Enter.</p>
        <div class="note">On Windows, if <span class="ic">claude</span> isn't recognized, try opening a new terminal window after installation.</div>

        <h2><span class="step-num">4</span> Install Your Skills Bundle</h2>
        <p>Unzip the bundle and navigate to its folder in your terminal.</p>

        <h3>macOS / Linux</h3>
        <div class="code-block"><code>bash install.sh</code></div>

        <h3>Windows (PowerShell)</h3>
        <div class="code-block"><code>.\install.ps1</code></div>

        <p>The installer copies all 50 skills to the correct location automatically.</p>
        <p>Verify installation:</p>
        <div class="code-block"><code class="comment"># macOS / Linux</code>
<code>ls ~/.claude/skills/

<span class="comment"># Windows</span>
dir $env:USERPROFILE\.claude\skills</code></div>
        <p>You should see 50 skill folders listed.</p>

        <h2><span class="step-num">5</span> Your First Project</h2>

        <h3>5.1 Create a project folder</h3>
        <div class="code-block"><code>mkdir my-first-project
cd my-first-project</code></div>

        <h3>5.2 Start Claude Code</h3>
        <div class="code-block"><code>claude</code></div>
        <p>You'll see Claude's greeting and a <span class="ic">&gt;</span> prompt.</p>

        <h3>5.3 Try your first commands</h3>
        <div class="code-block"><code><span class="comment"># Explore an existing codebase</span>
<span class="cmd">&gt; /onboard-codebase</span>

<span class="comment"># Plan a feature</span>
<span class="cmd">&gt; /task-breakdown Add user authentication with JWT tokens</span>

<span class="comment"># Code review</span>
<span class="cmd">&gt; /code-review</span>

<span class="comment"># Write a commit message</span>
<span class="cmd">&gt; /commit-message</span></code></div>

        <h2>How to Use Skills</h2>
        <p>Skills are invoked with a <span class="ic">/</span> prefix:</p>
        <div class="code-block"><code>&gt; /skill-name [optional argument]</code></div>
        <p>Some skills work on their own. Others need context:</p>
        <div class="code-block"><code>&gt; /fix-error TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'map')

&gt; /debug-smart The API call returns 200 but the UI doesn't update

&gt; /explain-code [paste the function you want explained]</code></div>

        <h2>All 50 Skills — By Category</h2>

        <h3>Code Quality</h3>
        <div class="skill-table">
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/code-review</span><span class="skill-desc">Systematic review with severity levels</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/security-review</span><span class="skill-desc">OWASP-based security audit</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/performance-review</span><span class="skill-desc">Find N+1, memory leaks, slow patterns</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/refactor</span><span class="skill-desc">Identify and fix code smells</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/clean-code</span><span class="skill-desc">Naming, functions, error handling reference</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/solid-principles</span><span class="skill-desc">SOLID principles with examples</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/tech-debt</span><span class="skill-desc">Catalog and prioritize technical debt</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/accessibility</span><span class="skill-desc">WCAG 2.1 AA checklist</span></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Debugging</h3>
        <div class="skill-table">
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/debug-smart</span><span class="skill-desc">Scientific debugging method</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/fix-error</span><span class="skill-desc">Error decoder + stack trace reading</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/trace-bug</span><span class="skill-desc">Five Whys root cause analysis</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/memory-leak</span><span class="skill-desc">Detect and fix memory leaks</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/async-debug</span><span class="skill-desc">Diagnose Promise and async/await bugs</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/typescript-errors</span><span class="skill-desc">Decode TS2345, TS2322 and more</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/regex-helper</span><span class="skill-desc">Regex reference + common pitfalls</span></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Documentation</h3>
        <div class="skill-table">
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/generate-docs</span><span class="skill-desc">Write docs for any code</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/jsdoc</span><span class="skill-desc">JSDoc/TSDoc tag reference</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/readme-write</span><span class="skill-desc">Write a proper README</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/api-docs</span><span class="skill-desc">Document REST APIs</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/changelog</span><span class="skill-desc">Generate changelogs from git history</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/explain-code</span><span class="skill-desc">Explain code at 3 audience levels</span></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Testing</h3>
        <div class="skill-table">
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/write-tests</span><span class="skill-desc">Write unit tests (AAA pattern)</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/edge-cases</span><span class="skill-desc">Find edge cases you missed</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/mock-generate</span><span class="skill-desc">Generate test mocks and fakes</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/test-coverage</span><span class="skill-desc">Analyze coverage gaps</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/e2e-tests</span><span class="skill-desc">Playwright/Cypress test patterns</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/test-data</span><span class="skill-desc">Generate realistic test data</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/snapshot-tests</span><span class="skill-desc">When and how to use snapshots</span></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Git &amp; Workflow</h3>
        <div class="skill-table">
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/commit-message</span><span class="skill-desc">Conventional Commits from staged diff</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/pr-description</span><span class="skill-desc">PR description from git log</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/git-cleanup</span><span class="skill-desc">Clean stale branches and history</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/merge-conflict</span><span class="skill-desc">Resolve merge conflicts systematically</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/release-notes</span><span class="skill-desc">User-facing release notes</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/branch-strategy</span><span class="skill-desc">Branch naming and gitflow patterns</span></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Architecture</h3>
        <div class="skill-table">
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/architecture-review</span><span class="skill-desc">Deep review with ADR output</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/design-patterns</span><span class="skill-desc">GoF patterns with TypeScript examples</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/api-design</span><span class="skill-desc">REST and GraphQL best practices</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/database-schema</span><span class="skill-desc">Schema design and migration patterns</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/microservices</span><span class="skill-desc">Service boundaries and distributed systems</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/dependency-audit</span><span class="skill-desc">Security and hygiene audit for packages</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/folder-structure</span><span class="skill-desc">Project organization by framework</span></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Security</h3>
        <div class="skill-table">
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/security-audit</span><span class="skill-desc">Full OWASP Top 10 audit</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/env-security</span><span class="skill-desc">Secrets and environment variable hygiene</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/sql-injection</span><span class="skill-desc">SQL injection prevention reference</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/auth-review</span><span class="skill-desc">JWT, sessions, RBAC patterns</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/csp-setup</span><span class="skill-desc">Content Security Policy configuration</span></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Productivity</h3>
        <div class="skill-table">
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/standup</span><span class="skill-desc">Prepare daily standup notes</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/task-breakdown</span><span class="skill-desc">Decompose features into tasks</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/onboard-codebase</span><span class="skill-desc">Rapid codebase exploration report</span></div>
          <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-cmd">/sprint-plan</span><span class="skill-desc">Sprint planning with capacity check</span></div>
        </div>

        <h2>Tips</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Be specific.</strong> "Fix the bug" has no context. "Fix the bug in <span class="ic">calculateTotal</span> — it returns NaN when the cart is empty" → Claude can help.</li>
          <li><strong>Give Claude context.</strong> Before a code review, describe what the code does. Before debugging, describe what you expected vs. what happened.</li>
          <li><strong>Use it for learning.</strong> Ask Claude to explain decisions: "Why did you use a closure here?" or "What's the trade-off between these two approaches?"</li>
          <li><strong>Chain skills.</strong> Write feature → <span class="ic">/code-review</span> → <span class="ic">/write-tests</span> → <span class="ic">/commit-message</span> → <span class="ic">/pr-description</span>. Complete professional workflow.</li>
          <li><strong>Review everything Claude writes.</strong> Claude Code is powerful but not infallible. Read the code before committing. You're the engineer responsible for the outcome.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Keyboard Shortcuts</h2>
        <table class="tbl">
          <thead><tr><th>Shortcut</th><th>Action</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Ctrl+C</td><td>Cancel current operation</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Escape</td><td>Exit current prompt</td></tr>
            <tr><td>↑ / ↓</td><td>Navigate command history</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Ctrl+L</td><td>Clear screen</td></tr>
            <tr><td>/help</td><td>Show available commands</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
        <p><strong>"claude: command not found"</strong><br>
        Node.js global bin isn't in your PATH. Try: <span class="ic">npx @anthropic-ai/claude-code</span> or reinstall Node.js from nodejs.org</p>
        <p><strong>"Invalid API key"</strong><br>
        The key may have been copied incorrectly. Go to console.anthropic.com and create a new key.</p>
        <p><strong>"Rate limit exceeded"</strong><br>
        You've hit the API rate limit. Wait a minute and try again.</p>
        <p><strong>Skills not working</strong><br>
        Check that skills are installed correctly: <span class="ic">~/.claude/skills/code-review/SKILL.md</span> should exist. Run <span class="ic">install.sh</span> again.</p>

